title: Add double ended queue (deque) to queues data structures
body:
### **Describe your change:**
This adds a double ended queue (deque) to the data structures under queues. A deque is effectively a doubly-linked list/queue/stack combination that only allows adding, removing, and peeking from the beginning and end. Because of the name, I chose to put this in the queue section (I don't believe it is large/important enough to warrant its own section)

title: Add Node generic superclass
body:
**Add Node generic superclass.**
There are a lot of Node classes that look very alike and most of them are private so they can't be reused. I suggest creating a generic Node class that is extended by all the Node classes. I also suggest creating a new package for development utilities like this new Node class and the SearchAlgorithm interface, something like 'DevUtils'.
